==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[pro]], ''[[before]]'' + [[testis]], ''[[witness]]''
===Verb===
{{wikipedia}}
'''to protest'''  (''intransitive'')
# to make a strong [[objection]]
#:''How dare you, I '''protest'''!''
'''to protest''' (''transitive'')
# to [[affirm]] something
#:''I '''protest''' my innocence.''
#(''mostly US'') to [[object]] to something
#:''They '''protested''' the demolition of the school.''
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A [[formal]] [[objection]], especially one by a [[group]]
# A [[collective]] [[gesture]] of [[disapproval]], sometimes [[violent]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[protest]] {{n}}
*French: [[protestation]] {{f}} (1), [[manifestation]] {{f}} (2)
*Slovene: [[protest]] {{m}}
*Polish: [[protest]] {{m}}
*Swedish: [[protest#Swedish|protest]] {{c}}

